Questions:
Which of the following procedures in the study is considered experimental?
A) Standard chemotherapy with high dose drugs for non-small cell lung cancer;
B) Low dose chemotherapy drugs for non-small cell lung cancer;
C) Routine blood and urine tests for monitoring health during chemotherapy;
D) Lung tissue biopsy for initial cancer diagnosis.

Correct answer: B

If you experience an injury as a result of participating in this study, whom should you inform?

A) Your primary care physician;
B) The study sponsor;
C) The study doctor or the Institutional Review Board (IRB);
D) Your insurance company.

Correct answer: C) The study doctor or the Institutional Review Board (IRB).
